Author: davidw
Content: Makes sense to me.  Know what you're getting into, discuss it and get the approval of your partner, but if it's what you're set on doing, you can probably find a way.  Tim O'Reilly started his company after the birth of his first child, if I'm not mistaken.  I don't suppose it qualifies as a "startup" in the sense of Google but he seems quite successful to me.
